| ID           | Validation Requirement                                                  | Control Information                                                                                          | Evidence Examples                                             | Related NIST SP 800-53 Controls                                  |
|--------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| KSI-IAM-01   | Enforce phishing-resistant multi-factor authentication (MFA)            | Enforces MFA methods resistant to phishing, such as hardware tokens or app-based authenticators.             | MFA configuration reports, authentication logs               | AC-2, IA-2, IA-2(1), IA-2(2), IA-2(8), IA-2(12), IA-4              |
| KSI-IAM-02   | Enforce strong passwords                                                 | Implements policies requiring complexity, expiration, and reuse restrictions on passwords.                   | Password policy documentation, audit logs                    | AC-3, IA-5, IA-5(1), IA-6                                         |
| KSI-IAM-03   | Use secure API authentication methods via industry standard protocols    | Uses OAuth2, OpenID Connect, or similar protocols to secure API authentication and authorization.            | API gateway logs, authentication method configs              | AC-14, IA-8, IA-8(1), IA-8(2), IA-8(4)                            |
| KSI-IAM-04   | Use a least-privileged, role-based, and just-in-time security model      | Enforces RBAC with minimal necessary privileges and JIT access provisioning for elevated rights.             | Access control reports, role definitions, access reviews     | AC-2, AC-3, AU-9, IA-11, PS-2, PS-3, PS-4, PS-5, PS-7, PS-9       |
